# Agent Terminology Standardization

## 🚫 Prohibited Terms
- **"sub-agent"** - All agents are equal, no hierarchical naming
- **"parent-agent"** - Use "invoking agent" or "calling agent" if context needed
- **"child-agent"** - Use "invoked agent" or "created agent" if context needed
- **"main-agent"** - Use "root agent" or "initial agent" if distinction needed

## ✅ Approved Terminology
- **"agent"** - The only standard term for all agent instances
- **"agent instance"** - When referring to a specific agent occurrence
- **"agent replica"** - When referring to agent copies/instances
- **"root agent"** - The first agent in an execution chain (if needed)
- **"invoked agent"** - An agent created by another agent (if context needed)

## 🎯 Naming Conventions
- Agent IDs: `agent_0`, `agent_1`, `agent_2` (numeric sequence)
- Agent copies: `agent_0_copy_1`, `agent_1_copy_1` (with copy notation)
- Variable names: `agentId`, `agentNodeId`, `agentNumber` (no sub/parent prefixes)

## 🔧 Code Comments and Logs
- Use "Agent" without qualifiers in most contexts
- Add context only when absolutely necessary for clarity
- Focus on the agent's role or function, not its hierarchical position

## 📋 Migration Guidelines
- Replace all instances of "sub-agent" with "agent"
- Remove hierarchical implications from variable names
- Update comments to use standardized terminology
- Ensure all agents follow the same lifecycle and patterns